---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About — Nosaka"
  description="Nosaka is a voice-first executive assistant, built around one standard: would a good human assistant actually respond this way?"
>
  <Header current="about" />
  <main>
    <div class="page-hero wrap">
      <h1>Built to actually listen.</h1>
      <p class="lede">Nosaka is a voice-first executive assistant — not a chat app with a microphone attached to it.</p>
    </div>

    <article class="article wrap">
      <p>
        A good assistant doesn't make you operate them. You don't fill out a form to ask a real assistant to move a meeting — you just say it, and it's handled. That's the standard Nosaka is held to: would an attentive, detail-oriented human assistant actually respond this way? Not a canned confirmation, not a wall of text read back at you — genuinely paying attention, and answering precisely and concisely, without extra ceremony.
      </p>

      <h2>Voice first, not voice added</h2>
      <p>
        Most "AI assistants" are text interfaces with speech-to-text bolted on. Nosaka is designed the other way around — every interaction is built for a spoken conversation from the start, which changes what gets said, how much, and when to just act instead of asking. <a href="/blog/voice-first/">More on what that means in practice</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Memory that actually reduces effort</h2>
      <p>
        Preferences shouldn't need repeating. Nosaka is built to remember how you like things done — your schedule's rhythm, how you travel, the small recurring details — and get quietly better at anticipating them, rather than treating every request like the first one.
      </p>

      <h2>Where things stand</h2>
      <p>
        Nosaka is currently in private testing — a small, deliberately unfinished product being refined in real, everyday use rather than polished for a big launch. <a href="mailto:hello@nosaka.ai?subject=Early%20access">Request access</a> if you'd like to try it early.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
